definition.value: A ketoaldonic acid that is rhamnonic acid which is lacking the 3-hydroxy group, has a keto group at the 2-position and L-configuration.
A chlorophenoxyacetic acid that is phenoxyacetic acid carrying a chloro substituent at position 4.
A 5-oxo-2-furylacetic acid having the C=C double bond at the 3,4-position.
A dihydroxybenzoic acid where the hydroxy groups are at the 4- and 5-positions together with a hexaprenyl group at the 3-position.
